[2
Date: Mon, 21 January 2001
From: C.H. Calisher <calisher@promedmail.org>
Subject: Wild goose die-off - USA (New Jersey): RFI

Has anyone considered the obvious possibility that this die-off and the
previous one were due to West Nile virus? Brants are geese and they
are dead and West Nile virus kills geese.
--
C.H. Calisher
AIDL, department of Microbiology
Colorado State University
Ft. Collins, CO 80523
e-mail: calisher@promedmail.org
[Anyone objecting that WNV is mosquito-transmitted & there were no
mosquitoes flying around biting birds in New Jersey in November
2000, has to explain the finding of WNV in a dead hawk in February
last year (2000), also when there were no mosquitoes active -- see:
West Nile virus isolated - USA (New York) 20000314.0359. - Mod.JW
